  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "I Saw You (Presented by The Improv Centre & The Georgia Straight)";
  schema:description """
	<h2>Wednesdays</h2><span><br/></span>A show based on the hopeful notes and letters of potential loves who shared lingering glances on public transit or flirtatious smiles while pretending to listen to their friend at a coffee date! This show will explore close calls, chance encounters and fateful rendez-vous with inspiration from YOU, our audience, and THEM, the hopeful romantics who have written into the I Saw You column of the Georgia Straight, believing that fate might just lead them back to their special someone.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Run time: 90 minutes including intermission<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Rated: 18A<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please Note: as The Improv Centre is a licensed facility, all minors (persons under the age of 19) must be accompanied by an adult.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All physical vouchers must now be redeemed via phone or email. Please contact the box office for assistance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/files/4902bb6c-01e0-4ad6-a3f4-245e1b0c43b6.jpg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
