<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/45601AKQVBSQHJBQRVBTCHVPGDDNQTRGL>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Improv 201: Mastering The Mid-form";
  schema:description """
	If you’ve seen one of our weekday shows, you’ve already met mid-form: 15–20 minute improv montages packed with big laughs and smart connections. In this 8-hour course, you’ll learn how we approach mid-form improv by exploring edits, callbacks, and ensemble work, all while building a cohesive 15–20 minute set from only a few suggestions. Expect lots of time on your feet; it’s time to get those reps in and master the mid-form! <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Saturday & Sunday 11am-3pm.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All workshops and classes are 19+ only.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">*Improv 103 is the prerequisite for Improv 201.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>REFUND POLICY:<span><br/></span>No refunds. Day one and two of training must be attended consecutively in the booked weekend to ensure a trusting and collaborative experience for all students. Completion of course and eligibility for class advancement requires full attendance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>LOCK OUT POLICY:<span><br/></span>Doors will lock 15 minutes after the class begins. Late comers will not be permitted.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All students must be at least 19 years old to attend.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>WAITLIST:<span><br/></span>If a class is sold out for a date you're hoping to attend, you can write in to <span class=\"BoldText\">boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca</span> to be added to a waitlist. While TIC can't guarantee you'll get a spot, we'll reach out if we can fit you in the class. 
""";
