<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/24401ANRSMNVVNPTCKDHLSQSTGQBDDKHJ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Heat Workshops";
  schema:description """
	<h2>Sign up for THE HEAT workshops!</h2><span><br/></span><h2>Wednesday 3:30-5:30pm  </h2><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Short form Games at TIC!</span> <span><br/></span>Workshop lead by Alan Pavlakovic and Emily Schoen from The Improv Centre<span><br/></span><ul><li>This workshop will be a crash course on the short form games that we play the most at The Improv Centre. Focusing on all our best tips and tricks, we will teach our favorite 3 - 4 player games to prepare you to jump on stage at The Improv Centre. </li><li>Experience Level: Intermediate/Advanced</li></ul><h2>Thursday 3:30-5:30pm</h2><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Relationships We Care About</span><span><br/></span>Workshop lead by Teresa & Folusho<span><br/></span><ul><li>This workshop looks at how to build authentic relationships based on scenes grounded in reality. We will discover the subtle beauty of truthful moments in comedic improv through useful skills, exercises and techniques. Finding the incredible moments in the seemingly mundane and exploring how to bring elements of you, your natural reactions and responses into the improv scenes through characters and comedy.</li><li>Experience Level: Intermediate/Advanced</li></ul><h2>Friday 1-3pm</h2><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Aggressive Support in the Universe of Your Show</span><span><br/></span>Workshop lead by Steve Plock, Linda Orr & Mike Geraghty from Dumb John<span><br/></span><ul><li>Playing hard or aggressively doesn't mean being loud or dominating the focus of the performance. Aggressive support is recontextualized as relentless support of your teammates ideas and your ensemble's voice. Students will learn how to contribute as sideline directors, secondary characters, background support, and more, in efforts to elevate normal scene work and group work into high concept universe building longform pieces. Listening, heightening, supporting, and sharing focus will be the key takeaways of this workshop designed to make each unique ensemble's performances go from great to grandiose. Students should have a good familiarity with longform play. Students should come prepared with a sensibility for quick play and focused support.</li><li>Experience Level: Intermediate/Advanced</li></ul><h2>Friday 3:30-5:30pm</h2><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Be ACE with Michelle Impro!</span><span><br/></span>Workshop lead by Jon Nguyen, Melissa Parker, Lilla Hodossy & Sabrina Luisi from Michelle Impro<span><br/></span><ul><li>Join Michelle Impro for a scenes-focused workshop, exploring how you can bring Action, Colour and Emotions (ACE) to your scenes. We'll work on each of these three elements and practice identifying which of them your scenes and show needs and when.</li><li>Experience Level: Intermediate/Advanced</li></ul><h2>Saturday 1-3pm</h2><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Wearing your heart on stage: How to make the world revolve around you(r character)</span><span><br/></span>Workshop lead by Jonny, Ryan & Bridie from Second Breakfast<span><br/></span><ul><li>In this fun and practical workshop participants will learn how to use strong emotion and truthful character choices to build interesting and fun worlds. Leaning into our signature Second Breakfast style and format, we’ll do heaps of grounded character and environment work to make sure that we’re setting ourselves (and our audiences) up for compelling and sustainable scenes.</li><li>Experience Level: Intermediate/Advanced</li></ul>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-01-28T15:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/files/3c724290-9859-4ae8-80d2-c9103a624692.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/location/603AMBLCJQMLRJDMDQKBNHDKQPPDPCQLJ>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/organization/the-improv-centre>;
  schema:url <https://theimprovcentre.ca/shows/>;
  schema:offers _:f1e5d4ebb48e4f06bccb5a907ecb5f635502;
  schema:duration "PT120M";
  schema:endDate "2026-01-28T17:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

_:f1e5d4ebb48e4f06bccb5a907ecb5f635502 a schema:AggregateOffer;
