formances go from great to grandiose. Students should have a good familiarity with longform play. Students should come prepared with a sensibility for quick play and focused support.</li><li>Experience Level: Intermediate/Advanced</li></ul><h2>Friday 3:30-5:30pm</h2><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Be ACE with Michelle Impro!</span><span><br/></span>Workshop lead by Jon Nguyen, Melissa Parker, Lilla Hodossy & Sabrina Luisi from Michelle Impro<span><br/></span><ul><li>Join Michelle Impro for a scenes-focused workshop, exploring how you can bring Action, Colour and Emotions (ACE) to your scenes. We'll work on each of these three elements and practice identifying which of them your scenes and show needs and when.</li><li>Experience Level: Intermediate/Advanced</li></ul><h2>Saturday 1-3pm</h2><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Wearing your heart on stage: How to make the world revolve around you(r character)</span><span><br/></span>Workshop lead by Jonny, Ryan & Bridie from Second Breakfast<span><br/></span><ul><li>In this fun and practical workshop participants will learn how to use strong emotion and truthful character choices to build interesting and fun worlds. Leaning into our signature Second Breakfast style and format, we’ll do heaps of grounded character and environment work to make sure that we’re setting ourselves (and our audiences) up for compelling and sustainable scenes.</li><li>Experience Level: Intermediate/Advanced</li></ul>
