<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/39601AJRRLKSVBMNJSKBSJSPPVNLVSKDK>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Rhinestone Golden Standard";
  schema:description """
	The Rhinestone Golden Standard is a glittering celebration of excellence, artistry, and unapologetic self-expression – all in support of a meaningful cause. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">This charity event brings together sensational drag performers and captivating variety artists for an evening where glamour meets generosity!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Expect jaw-dropping looks, powerhouse performances, and moments that shimmer long after the lights go down. From rhinestones and high drama to unexpected twists and crowd-pleasing spectacle, this show highlights artists who raise the bar while giving back to the community. Every act is thoughtfully curated to deliver a dynamic mix of drag, variety, and pure entertainment, creating an experience that is bold, inclusive, and unforgettable.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The show is hosted by Mr Gay Vancouver 46 Jay Kay and Ms Gay Vancouver 45 Mimi Anmormi<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With performances by:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Dandy<span><br/></span>Sophia Diamonds<span><br/></span>Indie Darling<span><br/></span>Ms Gay Vancouver 46 Fonda Vit<span><br/></span>Angel Jaden<span><br/></span>MX Black Ice<span><br/></span>Jamie Davis (Phyllis Hull)<span><br/></span>Burna Dart<span><br/></span>Mx Gay Vancouver 10 Wandering Pixie<span><br/></span>The Lucid Fairy<span><br/></span>Hailey Adler<span><br/></span>Shoop Dumplin'<span><br/></span>Todrick Masculinity<span><br/></span>Strawberry Short King<span><br/></span>Mr Gay Vancouver 46 Jay Kay<span><br/></span>Ms Gay Vancouver 45 Mimi Anmormi<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>*About The Rhinestone Phoenix Charity Foundation*<span><br/></span>The Rhinestone Phoenix Charity Foundation has been a part of the Vancouver LGBTQIA+ community since 1980, with our first Mr. and Ms. Gay Vancouver B.C. Richard McGuiness and Pussy Galore. The \"Gay\" titles were held under the advisement of the Dogwood Monarchist Society for the first four years.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Partial proceeds will be going to:</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">QMUNITY</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>QMUNITY, a Vancouver-based non-profit organization serving as British Columbia's queer, trans, and Two-Spirit resource center. It focuses on improving 2SLGBTQIA+ lives through free counseling, peer support groups, educational workshops, and community-building resources. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Friends For Life</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Founded in 1993, and built on the belief that no one should have to face the many challenges of HIV/AIDS, cancer and other serious illness alone, the Vancouver Friends for Life Society is a holistic wellness centre with a comprehensive list of support services. Our mission is to provide emotional, informational, spiritual, and practical support to people living with life-challenging illness. Our philosophy recognizes the connection between mind, body, and soul with a view towards supporting the whole person rather than focus solely on the illness. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Trans Lifeline</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Trans Lifeline is a grassroots, non-profit organization offering direct emotional and financial peer support to trans and nonbinary people in crisis. Run entirely by trans people, it provides a safe, confidential hotline (US: 877-565-8860; Canada: 877-330-6366) that operates without involving police, fostering a \"by trans, for trans\" community support model. The organization aims to improve the quality of life for trans individuals by providing connections, resources, and care.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Run time: 120 minutes including intermission<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Rated: 19+ (no minors allowed)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All physical vouchers must now be redeemed via phone or email. Please contact the box office for assistance.<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-02-22T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
